cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image reconstruction in magnetic resonance imaging. It also involves optimization strategies and parallelization techniques, which are common in the information theory (cs.IT) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Additionally, numerical analysis (cs.NA) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories may also be relevant due to the use of GPUs and real-time image reconstruction.
